<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-83-0929 </DOCNO><TEXT>A number of properties in the Albany/Colonie area have been identifiedas being potentially contaminated with uranium originating from the formerNational Lead Company's uranium forming plant in Colonie, New York. Theproperty at 23 Yardboro Avenue in Albany, New York (AL138) was the subjectof a radiological investigation initiated May 7, 1986. The property wasa residence with a one and one-half-story frame house located on a rectangularlot. An asphalt driveway or parking area is located at the east sideof the house. An area of {approximately}10 m {times} 14 m at the rearwas inaccessible. A diagram of the property showing the approximate boundariesand the 3-m grid network established for measurements outside the houseis shown. The lot included in the radiological survey was {approximately}14m wide by 36 m deep. Front and rear views of the property are shown.13 refs., 5 figs., 5 tabs.</TEXT></DOC>